&lt;p&gt;Gyffin Phlebotomist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen within Gyffin Surgery in Conwy for a part time Phlebotomist working 8 hours per week over 2 mornings (days to be confirmed), working with an enthusiastic team just outside Conwy Castle, this renovated Chapel is situated on the Woodlands in Conwy. The Practice is a Health Board run Practice with approximately 4,000 patients with a full compliment of receptionists / administrators and nursing team. We currently have regular locum GPs working in Gyffin but have now received interest for salaried GP positions. This has a warm and friendly atmosphere where you will be made to feel at home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date - 12th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact Debbie Searle, Practice Manager email debbie.searle@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01492 596381&lt;/p&gt;
